## Done

**32 tests passing** across 6 test files. All tasks in `specs/001-cli-lints-markdown/tasks.md` marked `[x]`.

### What was built

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `src/types.ts` | POD types: Diagnostic, Rule (LineRule + AstRule), Severity |
| `src/parse.ts` | remark-parse wrapper → mdast AST |
| `src/rules/trailing_whitespace.ts` | Line rule: trailing spaces/tabs |
| `src/rules/no_multiple_blanks.ts` | Line rule: consecutive blank lines |
| `src/rules/heading_hierarchy.ts` | AST rule: heading level skips |
| `src/rules/final_newline.ts` | Line rule: file must end with exactly one `\n` |
| `src/rules/index.ts` | Exports all rules |
| `src/lint.ts` | Engine: walks rules, collects diagnostics, isolates crashes |
| `src/format.ts` | `file:line:col: severity [rule] message` formatter |
| `src/cli.ts` | Entry point: args → lint → format → exit code (0/1/2) |

### Key decisions
- **Hybrid rule architecture** — line rules get raw text, AST rules get parsed tree
- **Rule isolation** — crashing rules produce error diagnostics, don't kill the process
- **Zero config** — all 4 rules on by default, no config file for MVP
- **Exit codes** — 0 clean, 1 issues, 2 tool error (per Unix philosophy)

